Zapatero to Link Spanish Wages to Productivity, Expansion Says

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-03-12T09:27:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-12/zapatero-to-link-spanish-wages-to-productivity-expansion-says.html
Spanish Prime Minister Jose Luis Rodriguez Zapatero will cede to demands by German Chancellor
Angela Merkel to link Spanish wages to productivity,  Expansion 
said, without saying where it got the information.  Zapatero informed European Union President  Herman Van Rompuy  of his intention in a letter, the newspaper said.    Spain  may also be considering starting a new set of anti-
crisis measures to speed up the recovery of its economy, the
newspaper said, citing unidentified EU sources.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ross Larsen at   rlarsen2@bloomberg.net  